
i. Create a class named Animal that has a method fur() which displays a message “I have fur all over my body.”

ii. Create another class named Dog that inherits from Animal and has a method bark() that displays “Dog barking.”

iii. Create another class named Puppy that inherits from Dog and has a method play() that displays “I play all the time.”

iv. Create an instance of the Puppy class and call the methods play(), bark(), and fur() in that order.



class Animal:
    def fur(self):
        print("I have fur all over my body.")

class Dog(Animal):
    def bark(self):
        print("Dog barking.")

class Puppy(Dog):
    def play(self):
        print("I play all the time.")

bosco = Puppy()
bosco.play()
bosco.bark()
bosco.fur()
